and the yelling, "Sir!

19:29.653 --> 19:31.586
Can you help me?! Am I close enough?!

19:31.655 --> 19:33.154
I'm not anywhere near the curb?!

19:33.256 --> 19:35.824
Okay, thank you, sir!" And so on.

19:37.094 --> 19:38.626
Do you have a second to talk?

19:38.729 --> 19:41.429
Yeah, you wanna unpack all
the Douglas and Poppy stuff?

19:41.531 --> 19:42.997
Wait, are you sweating?

19:43.100 --> 19:44.199
Are you wearing body spray?

19:44.301 --> 19:45.567
Yes, thank you.

19:45.669 --> 19:48.870
Um, I'm... I'm not here
to talk about them.

19:48.972 --> 19:51.106
Although dealing with their breakup

19:51.208 --> 19:54.109
made me think a lot about friendship,

19:54.211 --> 19:55.977
and... and relationships,

19:56.079 --> 19:59.428
and... complicated things, you know?

19:59.490 --> 20:01.649
And... And...
and I don't know, I just...

20:01.752 --> 20:05.120
I felt like I had to see you.

20:05.145 --> 20:06.188
Is that weird?

20:06.223 --> 20:07.322
No.

20:07.424 --> 20:08.508
I'm glad you're here.

20:08.558 --> 20:09.768
- You are?
- Yeah.

20:09.793 --> 20:12.278
I have been dying to tell you.

20:12.356 --> 20:14.591
Something crazy happened.

20:14.662 --> 20:17.896
